cs.DB, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.SI. 

This paper deals with keyword search in graph databases, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several CS sub-fields. The most relevant sub-category is likely cs.DB (Databases), as the paper proposes a new way to query graph databases without requiring knowledge of a query language or database schema. The paper also uses techniques from information retrieval (cs.IR) to rank search results based on relevance, and from artificial intelligence (cs.AI) to propose a bi-objective optimization approach. Additionally, the paper deals with graph algorithms (cs.DS) and optimization (cs.SI) to solve the proposed problems.
